caption: This spot sure knows how to satisfy their customers. Constantly with a super friendly mindset. The food is affordably priced, regularly delicious and clean.
Very good for take-out.
I generally get the Salmon Teriyaki, my partner generally gets a roll, sometimes we get appetizers. Reliably flavorful, fresh, and well prepared. And the staff is nice.
We had an awesome experience in this restaurant. We liked the great atmosphere and the meals. The staff members are super attentive. I am glad we eventually managed to visit this place.
Ordered takeout and the sushi rolls were excellent. We got the spider maki, house dragon roll, and makimono combo 2. They are a bit pricey but the quality is immaculate. Would definitely order again!
So gooood
Love this place. Sushi boat is amazing.
I tried this place once with my friend and I am hooked since then. I enjoy the awesome atmosphere and delicious food and drinks. They never disappoint.

The hibachi dinners from this restaurant are an ABSOLUTE DISGRACE! I have never been so disappointed in my life.  The meat was repulsive and the rice had no flavor whatsoever. I will NEVER order from there again.  I ordered medium rare steak and it was so over cooked I wouldn’t even feed it to a stray dog. I’m so upset.
Exceptional food, super nice employees, consistently good mood. They charge affordable prices and the food quality is excellent. Kudos.
I live close by just couple blocks from this place but this was my first time to try and the hype is real lol.
The quality of sushi and other food is great! This is one of my go to sushi restaurants. I strongly recommend and trust this restaurant
Excellent spot to get something when in a rush. The customer service is speedy, prices are reasonable, awesome vibes. Will come visit again

We keep going back. It is consistent and fresh. Good quality and friendly. We haven't been able to dine in the restaurant due to the pandemic and they don't have available outdoor space. We are looking forward to when we can!
I certainly enjoyed the food and customer service, great location close to my residence. The staff members are always very nice. Highly recommended.
Would definitely recommend trying this spot. Excellent vibes, fresh dishes, good service. Keep up the good work.
This place is great! Affordable rates, large portions and the staff are consistently very kind.
The food was amazing.  The staff is very helpful and friendly.  Overall a good experience.
Our favorite place for sushi 😍 The staff are wonderful and very attentive. The fish is always extremely fresh. Their tuna rolls and tuna sashimi are my favorite!! You really can't go wrong here!!
Delicious and fresh sushi.
Great food and great staff!

We met with friends at this spot for dinner. we heard about this spot from quite a few people.  Well, we were not disappointed. The crew welcomed us with a smile and we felt excellent. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we will definitely return to this restaurant. we highly recommend this place.

My girl friends and I picked Sakura as my birthday lunch spot and they did not disappoint! We started with the vegetable tempura which was delicious. I also had the white mountain sushi. It was some of the best sushi I've ever had! I can't wait to go back.
This spot constantly delivers. They have fresh dishes for fair pricing, there are no long waits even when the spot is full.
Excellent service, food was tasty, and they have menu items I've never seen it the states, or ever before! Try the Umesashi Maki.

The service and food was absolutely lovely with a wide variety of sushi. Does not have fried rice - which was not a deal breaker for me - but could be for some. Service was fast and perfect, and the bill wasn't too bad.
Never disappoints. Love the sushi here!
Awesome food, very nice staff, consistently  awesome vibes. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is fantastic. Keep it up.
Food is awesome

Tucked on a side street right off of busy Moody Street in downtown Waltham, we discovered a small, authentic Japanese restaurant. The extensive menu contains both cooked dinners as well as a variety of sushi. The service was polite and prompt.
Interesting renditions of Japanese dishes and sushi. Still uses plastic straws and farmed salmon.
One of my preferred places to grab something to eat. fantastic location, clean, and very good service. 5 stars!
THE best sushi we've had in or outside of Boston. They are super kind here! Only wish they served wine/beer for dine-in service but worth it either way.
Awesome sushi and ramen and great service will definitely go again.

Excited to place an order. Very disappointed and appalled when upon ordering a dish that stated it would come with vegetable tempura and it did not. NDB. Called to have the problem resolved and show proof of item description. The person I was talking to instead of kindly resolving the issue HUNG UP the phone on me. Never going back again. Also overpriced considering its low quality. Go into Cambridge for sushi instead. See screenshot and photo of dish for proof. So rude.
Decent. Sushi could have been fresher
If you have eaten Japanese food before, DO NOT COME. Or you will regret.
We got a takeout, my husband and I ordered the cold soba with shrimp & veggie tempura, sushi, and veggie dumpling. Everything was on point. Can’t wait to go there again.
Great food, super friendly

always order sushi from here and its soo good! all the times ive ordered, the fish esp the salmon have been realllly fresh. salmon sashimi portions are big and so fresh which is amazing because so many expensive restaurants have bad prices and quality. love this place for delivery but have never actually eaten there! oh and the delivery guy(s?) are so nice!

I went there for lunch.  Good food, good service.  I ordered miso soup and some sushi rolls.  The soup was good, the sushi was fresh, there was no added sugar to the rice (some places do that), and the wasabi was strong.  I am looking forward to going back.
Authentic food. Awesome taste.
Always cordial and prompt service. The sushi is very good.
Excellent Sushi and friendly service in a quiet, clean restaurant. Good choice for a business lunch or a meal with the significant other.
Sushi rolls are HUGE and delicious. Service was excellent.
Best kept secret, indeed! I had the sashimi plate. My friend had the salmon teriyaki. Finished with mango ice cream. Generous portions, fresh and tasty.
Best place for sushi in Waltham.

The big secret of Waltham! It wasnt fine dining, but it was excellent value. I had chirashi (raw fish over sushi rice in a bowl) and it was as good as anywhere else. Sushi and cooked foods were good too. Foods came with miso soup and a salad. Value! I scored a.parking right in front otherwise park on Moody. Big secret: 5% off when you pay cash!

One the best Sushi restaurants in Waltham.  The sushi is SUPER FRESH, the sizes meets expectations, and the staff is wonderful and super nice.  They have a wide selection of sushi.  They take care of you.  I always have the waitress  Fen there helping me with my food, she is super generous, super nice, and super friendly.  She is my go to person.  Their online ordering is also super simple and they give you a discount for to go orders.  I go there at least once a week.
The chicken teriyaki was good. Came with soup and salad. Good service.  Wasnt a fan of the noodles.
One of the best sushi places in the area! I highly recommend it. They also deliver via Grubhub which is great if you need lunch delivered at work!
Good sushi and not crazy expensive.

I ordered gyudon, katsudon and crazy maki. The beef is rubbery and worst rice I ever tasted - really disappointed! I have not tried the maki tho. Although, staffs are friendly, NO I will recommend this.
My favorite sushi place.
Special place. Went here for an anniversary and really enjoyed the food, environment, and service. Will be back soon.

We have eaten here several times. The sushi has always been good. We like the House Dragon roll (shrimp tempura, eel, avo). The unagi sushi had a bit more creaminess in the texture than I generally like, but the flavor was good and the eel sauce wasn't too sweet or overpowering. The one drawback is that they don't have a liquor license.
Great japanese food for a good price. Nice quiet atmosphere in a place with a cozy feel
Good and quite Asian place, recommende to visit
The sushi was awesome. Destiny was the name of the sushi that I had.
Bit of mixed review. Service was great, teppan was ok but my rice was not great. Also tempura butter and oil was not fresh so I felt sick afterwards.
First time, even though living in Waltham for more than 7 months. Food is good! But shrimp is not hot enough. I’d like to coming again.

4.5 STARS, actually. Quick and friendly service, with fresh sushi and plenty of options. Slightly impersonal and perhaps a bit rushed, but FAR more enjoyable and delicious than other options in town. I'll be back for the SCORPION ROLL, MAN!!!!
Good Soba! Good lunch menu.

I love both the quality of Sushi and most other items on their menu. The staff is very friendly, polite and helpful. They also do their best to adapt dishes to be gluten-free (I suffer Celiac disease).

Parking is horrible.  Dinner was excellent.  The magura was so fresh and good that I wish I had gone with an all sushi/sashimi dinner.  But I had some excellent fried pork gyoza,  and ended with a chicken miso ramen.  My ONLY complaint is that the chicken in the ramen was a bit dry.  I wish they had a shrimp ramen offering.  If I am ever in the area again I will definitely stop back for dinner. There is so much I want to try on their menu.
Good lunch deals , tasty sushi
Unexpectedly, great sushi at a reasonable price. My Daughter a connoisseur who was visiting me agreed.
Fusion = 5 stars. Taste = 4 stars.
Everything was excellent both the food and the service!

Good service and a good amount of food and portion size for the price. Great sushi and udon noodles! Lots of selection of sushi and sashimi, as well as hot foods on their menu. Usually it's pretty good, but one time it kind of disappointed? Maybe it depends on when you visit the restaurant.
amazing sushi very unique and different sushi options like no other restaurant.

Best sushi I've ever had, I order delivery from here very often and they always come quickly. The serving sizes are large. Also the restaurant itself is very nice, a great place to go for dinner. The people who work here are all so nice and welcoming. Can't say enough good things about Sakura!
Incredible ramen. Picturesque and my new bar for what good ramen should be.
Awesome food, nice atmosphere, and nice and helpful waitress! We will definitely be back!
Best Sushi in Waltham.  Very friendly staff

This review is based on my second experience ordering from here. The first time was excellent. This time, not so much. First order was over 60$ and this order was near 90$. Not a small deal.  Ordered online at 7pm on a Friday. I get that it is busy. ETA was an hour. An hour and 10 min later I called to get an update. She apologized and couldn't tell me when the delivery would arrive, other than "soon". 25 min later I called again and she said she would have to call the driver. At that point its just after 8:30. I wanted to cancel my order since apparently I would have an indefinite wait time. When I said I didn't care for the order at this point, she hung up on me.  There are so many other ways this could have been handled. Like, how do you hang up on a paying customer? Why not offer a discount or next time free or if they are that busy say that the normal delivery times DO NOT apply at this time and warn me that it could be longer or that they do not have delivery because they are so busy. Pretty much anything other than hang up on me.  The driver arrived about 10 min later as I was writing this review. I told him I called the restaurant and cancelled my order and the woman hung up on me so at this point I definitely am not proceeding with giving them my business.  He came to the door again and said the manager said to take $20 off. At the same time, my cell phone rang, and it was, I assume, the manager. She said sorry and to take $20 off. I told her the other person hung up on me and said they need to work on customer service etc.  So I went back and added one more star to make it two stars. My original review as I was typing had one star. Even though the manager attempted to correct the situation after I was already hung up on and waiting way too long, it was a bit too late. I still have a bad taste in my mouth, and it's not from the fish. The food is actually excellent, the portions huge and highest quality, and that is why I was so excited to order from them again. I am new to the area and was excited to find "my" new sushi spot. I am not sure I will order from here again. I am so disappointed and sad, really, because I loved the food.
Nice ambiance. The sushis are actually bite sized which is good, unlike other sushis where you have to split it.
Food is good and staffs are super nice.
(Translated by Google) Boston Lobster Roll is super delicious, it's fresh lobster!  (Original) 波士顿龙虾卷 超级好吃，是新鲜龙虾！
Great place that offers a wide range of food with great quality
Teriyaki chicken had no sauce
Today at Sakura for lunch I had the pork gyoza it was good and they had amazing service you should really come here!!!!
Cute little restaurant, great selection of sushi sashimi and maki!  Will definitely return
Very tasty food, fast serving. The only thing I'd change is the music, pop does not fit this place. Classics or Japanese would be better.

A quiet dining experience with very attentive staff and food at a great price. The sushi rolls are made with precision and the menu is extensive. No Pink Lady is offered here, but they do offer torched rolls which are amazing. No alcohol is served here which could deter some people. Highly recommend!
Good place, great prices. Parking can be tricky but you can get lucky.
Sushi was fresh, nice presentation. Unfortunately, don't expect to be able to get any alcoholic beverage here. No hot Saki :(
The best combo sushi and sashimi. Avocado salad and spyce tuna roll
Very good and cheap for lunch if you take the 2/3 rolls menu. Perfect!
I love getting sushi here!
Good waitstaff service and very close to the movie theater, so a nice spot for a meal beforehand.
